caption: Great spot for a good and filling brunch! Price is fair for the portions definitely left satisfied. Service is welcoming, quick and friendly.

Took my wife here as a surprise. The only issue I have is that I wish they had a better location so there was more parking. Absolutely delicious filipino food, friendly outgoing staff who were knowledgeable of the cuisine, and a nice atmosphere. They have inside and outside seating and a great assortment of cocktails and filipino dishes. Come eat here if you wish to have a taste of Cebu. We had the Tapas and the Sigsig.

two days ago was our first time we came to that excellent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last. We enjoyed the evening very much with the courteous service, with the excellent  meal and fine drinks and with the modest price. We will definitely visit there soon.

Went to dinner here on a date, and it was great! The food was delicious yet unique. The staff was super friendly, and they went above and beyond to make our experience just the best. Also, not just the food was terrific but the ambiance and the vibe. We loved the dinner night and can't wait to come back again. Highly recommended!
Food and service were great. The lechon was awesome! The drinks, especially the sangria were fantastic as well.

It's a nice, cozy place with friendly staff.  The bartender was practically THE man of the place, and he was very pleasant.  The food was very good, delicious. The calamari was definitely a crowd pleaser. If you are up for an adventure with your taste buds, go there on a Friday or Saturday so you can try the sinfully delicious lechon, a slow roasted pork belly, served with pickled papaya.  I tried a couple of different cocktail drinks and they were good.  It's a place that stands out and worthy of being a favorite.

We ordered a weekend special this past weekend, and it was amazingly delicious! All ingredients were fresh and played well together, and the price was good for the portions we got. Next, we plan to try their wings from We're Winging It!

Go the Halo Halo; not overwhelmingly sweet. Banana ice cream reminded us about the banana paddy taffy. The du leche ice cream would be better. Jellies and coconut were great! The ube ice was a cool color but I don’t think it added anything special to dessert.
I really enjoyed their dishes. I always get excellent service here. The place is clean and the workers are always kind. I highly recommend this place.

We ordered a Christmas dinner from Cebu, and it was excellent! Technically, the dinner package was for four people, but we had it with six and were so full at the end. All the dishes (including deserts) were fresh, exquisite, and delicious at an affordable price. Thank you, Cebu, for feeding us on Christmas Eve and bringing a lovely experience!

Visited 8/22/2020.  Sat on the cute patio. Two huge rats waddled through casually.  I was horrified, along with the family dining at the table next to us, our server acknowledge the issue, apologized but never offered a table inside or maybe a drink to ease my nerves.  She did however let us know that an exterminator had been there prior to opening that day (so this is an issue obviously). Very uncomfortable experience after, could not enjoy my over priced appetizer, entree or drink.  I sat the rest of my time there with my feet up! You could hear the tussle of these rats, probably near the trap(s) in the gangway!  Very much regret not getting up and leaving after seeing the first rat.  I sent the restaurant a follow email which was never answered or acknowledged.  Pretty disappointing Cebu. 👎🏼 Now I understand completely that there is a rodent issue in the city of Chicago, but maybe patios like theirs shouldn’t be open if there is such an issue?
This place sure knows how to take care of their customers. Consistently with a helpful attitude. The food is reasonably priced, constantly yummy and clean.
Excellent Filipino food

We're just obsessed with the food in Cebu and enjoy their ambiance every time we go there! However, this review I'd like to give to their new chicken wings project. My husband ordered us different flavors, and we're thrilled at how delicious the wings were. Everything came out fresh and flavorful, and the price was affordable for the quality. Now, we're not just big fans of Cebu but their chicken wings at We're Winging It! We couldn't highly recomend it!

Hands down best Filipino food in Chicago! My parents are from Cebu, and I've been visiting their hometown since I was a kid. Cebu Chicago is the only place in town with delicious food and flavors that remind me of my childhood. I also like the chef's creativity, and their cocktails are fantastic too. Super friendly staff and the atmosphere is terrific. Glad we found something unique in our neighborhood and not the next pizza place.
I have bookmarked this place and never had a chance to go. Finally me and a group of my coworkers came here and I was glad to have tried this place out.

Great vibes and friendly service! Love bringing friends here, especially if they’ve never had Filipino food before. Loved every dish I’ve had here so far, their cocktails are also amazing! My favorite place in the city for authentic Filipino food. Highly recommend their tocino and sambag fries
Awesome vibes and very friendly service. The meals were crisp and delightful. Will definitely recommend this place to my friends. Convenient rates and big portions. Good job.

From the knowledgeable and friendly staff, great ambience, and delicious food, Cebu was absolutely excellent! I highly recommend the Bloody Mary (Sesame Oil, Calamansi), Pandesal with Ube Butter(!), Sizzling Gambas, and Halo-Halo! No need for less or extra seasoning or sauce. The Halo-Halo was the best I have had in Chicago. Texture of the shaved ice is on point and not "soupy."  Looking forward to come in for dinner or even check out the patio area.

It’s been a long time since we truly enjoyed and were blown away by a meal. Tonight, we dined outside at Cebu’s patio and everything we ate was delicious! Bartender, Will, was amazing and so accommodating. We’re so lucky to have Cebu in our neighborhood. Go support them!
Good food, in a cool location. Would be great in the Summer with their back patio 🙂

Amazing meal and very attentive, well-informed service last night. Our party of 4 went down the shareables menu and everything was light and cooked to perfection. Amazing cocktails as well, a new favorite spot in Wicker Park.
Great atmosphere and authentic Filipino food served creatively.  Highly recommend the beef tapa, BBQ, and chicken empanada.

We love eating out. Last night we arrived in this fine place which we didn’t know before. We spent a beautiful evening there with great food and an efficient stuff and  a professional chief cook. We  added this fine restaurant in our phone list  and we shall certainly go again soon. We deeply recommend.
Really great food and service!

Best Filipino food in Chicago! Our favorite is their signature lechon which is so delicious, juicy, and crispy. We're regular customers of Cebu, and all the dishes we've tried were to die for! The staff is very friendly, and the service is excellent. Couldn’t recommend it more!
Great service. Food was fabulous. Inventive cocktails,  try the ube mule.

Ordered the Tocino bowl, adobo bowl, 2 drinks and the halo halo  Amazing service. 5/5 Great atmosphere 5/5  Made a reservation and they were accommodating to push it back a bit because we had something come up.  The food came out before the drinks.  Looks like they’re still working on their flow here.  My partner ordered the mango drink and commented that it wasn’t as sweet as she had hoped it would be. She also said that it didn’t taste much like mango.  I enjoyed the drink I ordered (Cebu later?) wish it had more of a tamarind taste. Strong drinks if that’s what you’re going for.  The meals were great but too expensive for the prices paid in my opinion. Portions were a bit smaller than I expected.  Dessert was amazing. 5/5  I think moving forward we’ll come for drinks and dessert after eating somewhere else.
Excellent food. Fast and friendly service. Hidden gem.
Boujieeee Filipino food. White washed. Not quite authentic

Cebu was amazing! We had brunch on the patio and it was such a great spot. The food was so fresh! The chicken and waffles was the best chicken and waffles I’ve had in awhile. I loved the color of the syrups and the butter. My husband got the chorizo sliders and he was very satisfied. The portions were good and we each had a little bit left to take home. The service was great also. We will definitely be going back.
One of my go-to spots to eat. awesome location, well kept, and excellent customer service. I highly recommend them!

This restaurant is delicious! There has been explosion of Filipino eateries in the city over the past year, and this one definitely stands out as one of, if not THE BEST! Excellent food and really great service. We loved the coconut milk-based adobo, empanada, inasal skewers, and guava sangria! I hope to be back really soon.
Wonderful food and service, we are definitely going back! The Sambag chicken wings, pork skewers, and beef tapa were stand outs for me but everything was so good! Do not miss dessert either, yum!
Happy hour until 630pm. Appetizers are good. Patio is spacious and shaded.

Nice patio for our first dining out in 3 months. Menu is small, but tasty and unique. The Mango Pavlova Float we had for desert is a string recommend. Empenadas are tasty and a nice change from others I have had.

We just love Cebu! Fantastic food - all options we had were delicious and sharable. The fact that this place is a family-run restaurant makes it more appealing to us since we try to support small local businesses. The staff is super friendly and accommodating, and their patio (with a great vibe) is dog friendly which is a huge plus. Cebu became one of our regular spots in the neighborhood, and we highly recommend it.

If you’re looking for a beautiful and intimate outdoor patio that has creatively killer Filipino fusion cuisine, Cebu is the place for you! Family owned and run - the food, drinks, staff and atmosphere go well above expectations. This was the first place my fiancé and I dined after the reopening and I couldn’t have felt more comfortable. The tables were set more than 6 feet apart so it didn’t feel crowded compared to the vibe of other restaurants in the area. Definitely add this place to your list ! And add the sweet chorizo pandesal sliders to your order immediately !

Cebu became our favorite spot in Wicker Park! We love not just the food but the atmosphere there. The food is incredibly delicious and comes in a generous size. Last time we had a roasted belly pork "lechon" (our #1 choice in Cebu), the meat was tender, and the skin was crispy, which made a perfect combination. We were wondering what the chef's secret of making this dish so tasty is? :)  Our other favorite options are chicken adobo and spicy sliders. Next time we plan to explore different choices. Lastly, the desserts are phenomenal, and the cocktails are refreshing too.
Great food! Ordered ahead for pickup. Had the adobo chicken and Ube cookie. Both amazing! Excited for more!
Great family run spot. I meant to take a picture of the chicken adobo for posterity, but I devoured it before that could happen. The garlic rice was savory deliciousness too.

We ordered takeout from Cebu during quarantine and they did not disappoint. The people were friendly and the food was phenomenal. We ordered the lumpia, pancit, and spicy chicken sliders and loved everything. We are looking forward to planning our next visit and trying the rest of the menu!
Heard good reviews but was disappointed overall.  Mezcal cocktail was tasty.
Very well organised and convenient spot. They serve generous meals and for fair rates. We liked the menu a lot and the staff were super personal and chatty. Highly recommended.

Trying to find a decent Filipino restaurant in the city of Chicago is harder than you think. Since the city is such a huge melting pot of people and cultures, you generally have specific areas where you'll find certain types of cuisine. Luckily, enter Cebu with reminiscent flavors of traditional Filipino cuisine, as well as modern spin of classic dishes. Take their Chicken and Waffle for example: inclusive of boneless deep fried chicken, it's paired with an untraditional Pandan syrup and Ube butter. You can space the regular waffle for a Ube waffle and get Ube syrup as well. I decided to over indulge and got all the fixings! If you want to try their Lechon, go for the Lechon Benedict on their brunch menu. It's decently sized and definitely shareable. You don't need to order the half/whole portion. If you're going to aim for dessert, the The Churro Bowl is good but tiny. When it arrived on the table, I was taken back a bit. Had I known the size, I would've ordered another dessert without hesitation.

It's the perfect mix of neighborhood gem and truly nicely done Filipino food. Filipino food in a outside dining experience is just not accessible and yet they are elevating the experience while making it familiar.
Very elegant and convenient spot. They serve big portions and for reasonable rates. I loved the meals very much and the waiters were super attentive and chatty. I recommend this place.
Great food, great staff.

Terrible service. We went during restaurant week, so the restaurant should have been aware that there would be large crowds. There was one server (who doubled as a host) for the whole floor. Both our server and the food runners rushed us, and were unable to answer questions about the menu. Further, not one plate was cleared off of our table. This means that we had to maneuver around duck bones and dirty utensils to eat our dessert.  Presentation of food was good, though the food itself was lukewarm at best.  Will not go back.

This place is the one I always prefer. I visit plenty of restaurants but here I go the most. The crew is very welcoming and the cooking they cook is so flavorful. I am always happy to have a decent dinner in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.

Cebu was awesome! We came for restaurant week and split the veggie lumpia, moringa pasta and flavors of turon. They were all delicious!! The dessert was so impressive and artful! We had the whiskey shakes and butterflies in the attic for cocktails and they were AMAZING! The setting is very cozy and comforting. We will definitely be back to try more!
Love this place.
It was good not great but good
One of my preferred spots to eat. excellent location, well kept, and excellent customer service. I recommend this place!

Unfortunate unpleasant experience with their restaurant week menu. Some lingering thoughts include, the lack of service and attention to detail, the heavily salted pasta, the dry duck, and the undercooked rice. Thankfully the desert was perfect enough to sweetened up the end of the night.
Best Filipino food around! Don't have to go way north anymore! Come here and you won't regret.

I dine in this place from time to time! This is my favorite place to have a bite.  I go to this spot frequently. The cooking is very tasty, the workers are friendly and the payment is affordable. I enjoy meeting in this place for a good meal.
Exceptional and tasty food, I loved the atmosphere this spot has, and the workers were welcoming. I will surely eat here again.

We ordered the Sambag Wings, the Sisig, and the Lechon Manok to share. The Wings were hot and fresh, definitely the highlight. The Sisig was a bit dry and not as hot as the amount of jalapeños led me to believe. The Manok had good flavor, but was outdone by how much better the Wings were.  The ambiance of the place is quite nice, dim lit and relatively lively (this was a Thursday dinner).
This spot never fails to impress. They serve good dishes for affordable rates, there no long wait even when the spot is loaded.
Legit Filipino food for dinner in Wicker Park. Hella flavourful and expertly cooked.  BBQ Skewers - Sisig - Sambag Wings - Bam-I  The sisig and the wings were my favourites

I visit this unique restaurant many times since I enjoy the ambiance that is outline this place. The staff is extremely cordial and skilfull. The service is pretty fast. Most important, the food they serve is perfect. I have been there many times and I was always satisfied. The pay is modest. I highly suggest this place to to all.
We had a superb time in this restaurant. We liked the extraordinary ambience and the menu. The staff are super personal. I am content we finally decided to eat here.
The customer service is consistently fast, good character, very kind employees. I will visit here again when I get in the area.
Lovely cultural dining experience. True authentic Philippines cuisine with a modern fusion twist. Not a very large establishment, but cosy and welcoming. Service was good and very friendly.
Great Filipino food!
Great to see a Filipino eatery in Wicker park -- prioritize the pancit and empanadas you won't regret it!
Delicious cocktail and awesome food! I will be back to try the desserts.
Good food

The other reviews of Cebu complain about high prices and poor service - neither of which relates to my 3 star rating. Our service was attentive and we got a lot of food for a reasonable price. The best dish we had by far was the chicken adobo, which was well cooked and flavorful. Unfortunately, the BBQ skewers were very fatty. The pork belly was unique and had a layer of very crunchy skin on the outside which was a fun sensory experience, but the pork belly was not cooked down very much so the large amount of fat was overwhelming and not soft and tender. The pork belly was bland without the sauce. Overall, I had hoped for bolder flavors and to be amazed by the experience.
Excellent cocktails. Cozy atmosphere and friendly staff. Great patio in warm weather. Food was tapas-style. Beef and Shrimp were my favorite dishes.
nice place to bring friends and introduced them to filipino regional food.

I was thoroughly impressed with Cebu! Great food, nice atmosphere and outstanding  service! The staff was so accommodating and the owner was extremely friendly too. We ordered a couple of items we shared. Cebu’s lechon (the roasted pork) is a must have, so juicy and crispy in the same time. Also, we really loved sisig and the barbecue skewers. Every single bite was AMAZING! Their shaved desert halo-halo and the cheesecake were so delicious too. Lastly, we had some very cool and unique cocktails that I think I’ve never tried anywhere in Chicago. Cebu has become one of our favorite restaurants in Bucktown/Wicker Park!
Good food great service.

Delightful Surprise! A great addition to a culinary adventure in Wicker Park.. My first visit and I'm already planning to my next. Still have a long list to go before I've tried everything on the Menu
Bam- i for me was too salty.. the chicharon in their sisig was already "hupas", deff not crunchy.. but the sisig as a whole was really good my husband enjoyed it.. i love the butterfly drink!

I would much prefer a more laid-back Filipino restaurant in the neighborhood, personally, rather than a slightly upscale place; if I'm going to pay $11 for halo halo, it better be the best I have ever had. The entrees are a la carte, so no bread, no rice comes with them. We shelled out for the bread, as it is a kind of bread that isn't easy to find around here and is pleasingly reminiscent of the milk bread I knew and loved in Tokyo, but didn't want to shell out for the rice as well--although the chicken adobo doesn't really make sense without it. Their take on pancit, Bam-I, would do better with more vegetables and less meat, or at least that option, as well as better separation of the rice noodles--the dish we were served had several clumps that bordered on inedible. The flavors on the whole were good, and as this place is pretty newly opened perhaps a little time will refine or expand their menu. As it stands, it is not likely we will return to pay $9 for six small lumpia. Additionally, our server asked if there were any dietary concerns and I told him I was allergic to corn. We then ordered the bread that he neglected to tell us had cornmeal on the top, and had to ask to find out. Two stars lost due to this fail.

The moment I stepped inside this vibrant place, lit felt like home. Going into details, the lechon belly was juicy, crispy, and perfectly tasty Cebuano style. Lechon manok was great, and lastly, the Halo-Halo was my favorite of all, it’s creamy, rich and smooth. Service is super fast, didn’t have to wait long at all. Shout out to Cody who went above and beyond for his service. Also to Marlon who was so accommodating and very friendly. Will strongly recommend this place to all who live in Chicago and those who are visiting Chicago!
Amazing food and great customer service!

We were really pleasantly surprised with this food. We ordered three dishes to share between two people as they mentioned everything was made to be shared, and it was way more than enough for both of us. We aren't familiar with authentic Filipino food, so I can't speak to the authenticity. However, the meat was super flavorful, tender, and juicy. We also ordered cocktails, and they were done really well and were pretty strong. The inside was designed pretty nicely, so there's a good ambiance in there. We didn't get to sit outside, but the back patio looked pretty nice as well. Overall, I would highly recommend checking this place out. It's definitely unique and high quality.
Food is good and has amazing flavor, but the portions are extremely small. The drinks are delicious. Upscale and modern Filipino food, but doesn't feel or taste like home. Don't forget your roots!

Unfortunately did not have a great experience at this place. The Lechon belly was tough and chewy, the beef tapa and sisig too salty, and the rest of the food was just ok. I would say my favorite were the chicken adobo and their cocktails. The service was also just ok - our server was trying his best, but restaurant was severely understaffed and you can hear arguments happening between kitchen staff and manager.

Got the lechon pork belly, chicken + waffles, and bam-i. Everything was pretty good. Pleasantly surprised by the chicken + waffles actually. Shakoy for desert was fantastic. Portions were satisfying as well.  Overall, pretty tasty and unique menu items. Service was also v good! Will most certainly be back at some point.

Love the garden dining experience - such a welcome surprise! The food was great. The food has authentically Filipino flavors but with an added flare to make you feel like you're dining out rather than having dinner in your grandmother's kitchen. I had the lechon manok which was so juicy and flavorful on its own I had to remember to use the accompanying dipping sauces and my husband had the sisig which he said was cooked perfectly. The halo halo can't be beat here. I'd pass on the pandesal which wasn't soft enough in my opinion, but otherwise I'd come again. Portion sizes were generous, though I still managed to eat everything on my plate. Order your entrees with a side of the garlic fried rice.
Try the LECHON BELLY. Crispy skin, tender & tasty pork.  Don't forget the fresh Mango Pavlova & HaloHalo! Staff was attentive, friendly, & knowlegeable about the food.

I won't recommed this place to anyone.  Their food is like a turo-turo in Philippines.  Lechon ek ek manok---- very dry! Sisig --- very salty and I don't understand the taste I guess the liver was not even fresh! The lumpia--- crispy but too oily! The enchalada --- so so! The beef tapa - salty! And we paid 70+ dollars not even worth!  This restaurant reminds me of cheap canteen in High School.
Excellent food, great service !!
Fantastic food, very knowledgeable and friendly staff.
Fun food and great prices. I really hope this place succeeds

Great food, interesting things that I had never had before.  I have not had a lot of Filipino food though, so don't know how it compares to other Filipino restaurants, but I would definitely go back and recommend this place to others.

I was disappointed at the food we tried. Specifically the sisig and lumpia. If you've had good authentic Filipino food, you're not going to appreciate this place much. The sisig is overfilled with onions to the point that you can't taste the pork. the lumpia was okay, not good enough to cost $9 for the six pieces. The pork bbq was the only good thing we had, but for the price, it's not worth coming back. I haven't tried anything from the special menu since they sold out on the pork bellies and the lechon manok. The cocktails look good, but I haven't tried it. If you're here to experience good Filipino food, let alone Cebuano food, I don't think you'll get it. I'm giving it 3 stars in the hope that the food I missed out on is good.

Fantastic dining experience with delicious food and cocktails and a beautiful and cozy dining atmosphere.  We ordered the Beef Tapa, Chicken Adobo, Bam-I and garlic rice.  Serving sizes were plentiful and we were all able to share.  Cocktails were full of flavor and I love that they use bamboo straws...have to keep those sea turtles safe on Apo Island!  The patio looks like a great place to dine, rain kept us inside.

Excellent Filipino food in a beautiful backyard patio. Servers were super attentive and friendly. Seems like a great spot for a casual hang out with friends during the summer.  I ordered the Average Joe cocktail, which despite its name was anything but average. It was not too sweet and fairly strong. I loved the addition of the dried mango too.  I had the lechon belly with steamed rice for my main entree. The meat was super juicy and paired excellently with the sauces. I can't speak to the authenticity of the dish, but the Filipino patron next to me noted that it was similar to how her father made it at home. A caution to others: this meal is big and likely meant for two, unless you're particularly hungry.  I also saw another customer eating the Halo Halo, which looked phenomenal. I would have ordered it but I was way too stuffed from my main entree alone. I'll definitely order this the next time I come!

Great Filipino restaurant - and I'm so happy that they opened in Chicago. Very authentic and ingredients are super high quality. I loved every dish I've tried (noteworthy are the sisig, lechon belly, Halo Halo). Will keep coming back and bringing friends :)
Food

We are from Indiana, we don’t know that we need to have a reservation. Just sad though, we are starving but we never got a response and don’t get seated. At least tell us to make a reservation or tell us the wait time.

Tldr: go to Isla Pilipina instead. The food here is fine to good. The chicken adobo was moist and flavorful, and the desserts were fantastic. However, it is not enough to justify the high prices. $9 for 7 pieces of lumpia? $25 for lechon? You can get the same quality food, if not better, at Isla Pilipina or other "old school" restaurants in the city, which also have more variety (there are only a handful of dishes on the menu at Cebu). I admit I came in with high expectations and that perhaps my standards are too high, but with other options for Filipino food in the city, I really cannot justify eating here.

Loved the food.  Owner and staff were friendly and helpful.  Great Wicker Park space with just a dozen or so tables and another 10 spots at the bar.  Patio out back looks cute.  Loved the beef skewers, the chicken and pork belly.  Grab a group.  Will be back to try their brunch!  While there a chicago food critic who had reviewed them a few weeks back was there picking up food.  That's how good it is.

Pandesal was very good. The sisig, chicken, and lechon roll were cooked well but under flavored. To someone who had never had these flavors, it's probably a good introduction for them.   For me, it was a little meh, underflavored, and small portions.  The papaya salad accompaniment was a nice surprise. Halo halo was lacking something too, not sure if the flan was made in house as it seemed more like mexican flan than Filipino flan. One of the owners was hanging around the dining room and there were only a few tables and he didn't say hello to anyone.  The wait staff was very nice. Try it if you've never had Filipino food before.
Awesomeness!!

It was a nice low light place with a very welcoming atmosphere. Great service. Met the owner as well. Loved hearing his story. The food was delicious, we literally had 1 of everything off the menu. My favorite was the chicken inasal!
The food came out cold, the sisig was at most ok, and the main entree of lichon was monotonous. A star for the great service and an additional for the atmosphere.
Everything was really good.  The chicken Adobo with garlic rice was so good.  Halo halo for dessert was the perfect ending. Would have enjoyed  larger portions.

This place is amazing! The food was reasonably priced with generous portions. The BBQ pork skewers were to die for! We also loved both their cranky cookies and their Halo Halo. We'll definitely be back next time we're in Chicago!
The worst service and food was  super blend I’ve had cebu food before and this isn’t  quite the taste and  frankly  It’s expensive.
Food was absolutely delicious - completely unexpected flavors. Dessert was incredible... The atmosphere was great and cozy place... very friendly servers and workers... Very reasonable prices.
Delicious food. Its a new restaurant, they need to work out some kinks. They need way more staff. But definitely stop by for food and drinks.
Great atmosphere and service.  Food was excellent!
Great place! The food and the service are amazing! Very friendly with an awesome vibe! I had bbq skewers, pandesal bread, a red Horse, and Halo Halo! Delicious!!

Had a reservation for 9:45pm. They ran out of chicken inasal and garlic rice, that was understandable since they just opened so the chaos was expected. We got the kinilaw, sisig and pork skewers. The kinilaw was too bland. It was missing some flavor. The sisig had a strong bitter after taste because it had liver. It didn't go well together it just ruined the sisig. I don't know why it had jalapenos in it also. It should be the small chili peppers like the thai ones. The pork skewers were ok, not the best. They were tender but so tiny. The atchara or whatever that was they served with it was so bland. The food was way too pricey for the portions they give you. I wouldn't mind if the food was actually great and worth it but it wasn't. We didn't bother with desserts anymore. We already knew we'd be disappointed at that point. This place would probably be good if you've never had awesome Filipino food before. Not going back for sure.
Great food and drinks, staff is super friendly. Great place for semi romantic dinner or to just grab a few drinks :)

Delicious food! I have been to the Philippines and several Filipino restaurants here in Chicago, NYC and LA, and this place is a real  gem.  First of all, PORK BELLY is a MUST to try! Tender, juicy and in the same time crispy with great taste. Another dish that impressed our minds was SISIG. It had such a splendid blend of flavors, crisp and not too spicy.  Finally, we ordered two deserts (halo-halo a calamansy tart). It was a great culmination of the dinner. The halo-halo was the best I’ve ever tried in my life and the tart had a very delicate and delicious taste.  I’ll be coming here again and again!

After hearing for this new restaurant, I was eagerly anticipating it's arrival on the Chicago food scene, especially since this place represented the style of Filipino cooking my family immigrated from. Overall, some dishes were good, some just fell flat. I'm not sure if we just happened to get some off dishes for the night but, even so, that's no excuse. First, I'll start off by saying that I love the space. The staff was friendly and the service was great. I came with a group of friends, some Filipino, some not. Some of the dishes we wanted to try out were already sold out. So maybe those were knock out dishes that might have changed our experience. We ordered some appetizers (lumpia, pork skewers, pandesal (bread), and a salad with duck egg). Unfortunately, the lumpia, which is like a Filipino eggroll was crispy on the top and a bit soggy on the bottom. That usually means it was sitting too long to cool off. The rest of the apps were good. As for main dishes, we ordered the Sisig and that was a bit disappointing. It's supposed to be served searing hot (imagine a steak fajita platter) topped with an egg. It was just warm and the texture was a bit off. It didn't have the flavorful meat or crunch you would expect with it. The chicken adobo was ok. I think they added coconut milk to it which I think made it a little more creamier and lost the punch that you'd expect in flavor of soy sauce, vinegar, and garlic. The chicken was cooked well though. The thing that disappointed us the most was the Pork Belly. I've read other reviews and people seems to love it. What makes pork belly amazing is the crackling crunch of the skin, and that fat of the pork melts into the meat, so it's really juicy and flavorful. Our was the opposite. The meat was dry and the skin was rubbery. We immediate knew it was not good when we tried to cut into the skin and it felt like cutting rubber. The dinner ended on a high note in which we all enjoy Halo-Halo (a dessert worth coming for). For those who don't know anything about Filipino food, they'll walk away thinking it was a good meal. For someone like me who is open to Filipino culinary fusions, making a twist on classic dishes, etc....the entrees we had fell flat. I did make plans with another group of friends to check this place out, so I'm giving it another shot. I hope it's better the second time around.

I wish I could have had a better experience. Maybe it is the fact that this restaurant newly opened or that it might have been an off night.  We ordered the Kinilaw (Ceviche) appetizer, the Chicken Adobo and Pork BBQ skewer entrees, a side of garlic rice and a glass of wine and a cocktail drink.  We received the side of rice before the appetizer came, then the ceviche 10 minutes later. Finally after about 25 minutes we received the chicken adobo.  The second entrée, the BBQ skewers never arrived. We had also ordered an extra glass of wine that didn’t arrive. After starring at the empty plates for an extra 20 minutes the waitress asked if we wanted dessert even though the second entrée and the additional glass of wine never came. We asked if it was normal to have the side of rice come before all our food and the waitress told us that it was customary in Filipino cooking to receive the rice before anything else. We had spent the previous summer in the actual island of Cebu, Philippines and never experience this tradition.  We really wanted to like the neighborhood spot but the service was awful and the food wasn’t bad despite not getting the full order. Can’t recommend it unfortunately, hopefully they can address the bad service.

Food was fine. A couple of things tasted v good but not at all fine dining so go with that in mind. The pork mask was the best hands down.  Ceviche was surprisingly boring.  And I left smelling so bad from all the oil smells from kitchen....Wear machine washable tees and jeans!
The halo halo is worth the price of admission

Very nice place in Wicker Park. The ceviche was missing something with the flavor, but from there, everything was very good. The Pork Belly special was so good we ordered it twice! The Pork sliders were also fantastic, hope this place sticks around for a long time.

This dessert makes me proud of our lemonsito (bisaya for kalamansi) totally stand out and better to keylime pie in Keywest!! Very subtle with robust, tarty sour but sweet and not over powering. Also, the tanduay ice cream was amazing been mixing tanduay with vanilla ice cream for my cocktails with pineapple or mangos this one slay it!!

A great Filipino restaurant that's worth checking out. The menu is small, but it includes Filipino favorites and staples like adobo, lumpia, and sisig. All of the dishes were great, and the Filipino friends I was dining with felt like they were very authentic. Personally, I felt like the menu was lacking a noodle dish, like pancit. The service was also great - attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable.  The price was on the high side! But it was worth a splurge.
Awesome addition to Wicker Park!
